result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by parties and the defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 2 AMENDED
The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction, concurrent to any other sentence.

*Court ordered restitution in the amount of $1,545.26 to be paid to Metropolitan Maintenance Landscaping. Collection of restitution is to be monitored by the DOC and is to be paid during extended supervision for cases 12CF944 and 09CF3182. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Defendant to pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges; including the DNA surcharge. Collection of payments is to be monitored by the DOC and is to be paid during extended supervision for cases 12CF944 and 09CF3182. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

Filed, 
Crime Victim Impact Statement, Restitution Worksheet, and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.

AS TO COUNT 1
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the state, Court ordered Count 1 Dismissed, but Read In. 

AS TO COUNT 2 AMENDED
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Jury Instructions/Elements received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske in custody.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Parties have reached a resolution.

AS TO COUNT 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Attempt Theft (Value Not Exceeding $2,5000), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a) and 939.32, a Class A Misdemeanor.

Defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case heard off the record. Defense counsel requests case be set for plea and sentencing. Neither party requests to address the court on the record. Signed, Filed & Distributed, Agreed Upon Request for A New Court Date form. Case adjourned to Branch 46.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 30, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Colin P. McGinn in court, defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske not in court, in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant not produced.  Defense requests to schedule case for status.  Court orders case adjourned to Branch 46.  Status conference scheduled for May 21, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  
Defendant to have no contact with: Metropolitan Maintenance & Landscape;  SCU or his or her family.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  
Defendant Timothy Eugene Dowske in custody.  
Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Branch 46.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  
Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  
DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 22, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
